{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a3f1c9e2-6b4d-4e8a-9c2f-2f6a1d5b8e10",
    "name": "Strategos - Business Central API",
    "description": "Business Central (Dynamics 365) custom API endpoints for the Strategos integration, as provided by Sergio Gayan (Becentis Consulting) over email between 2026-06-30 and 2026-07-08.\n\n**URL pattern**\n`https://api.businesscentral.dynamics.com/v2.0/{tenantId}/{bcEnvironment}/api/{publisher}/{group}/{version}/companies({companyId})/{entity}`\n\n- `tenantId` = e9cf8bf3-1d78-4f23-94f9-9a494d01dc4e\n- `bcEnvironment` = RESTSTR (sandbox/test, confirmed working) or PRODSTR (production, not yet validated with these credentials)\n- `publisher` = strategos (this replaces the generic \"craze\" placeholder from the base BC API)\n- `group` = integrations\n- `version` = v1.0\n- `companyId` = c88d2c0c-2a25-ef11-9f88-6045bddecfa1 (corrected value from Sergio's 2026-07-08 email; an earlier value, 8d69f51b-e5a1-eb11-9d03-00505627a590, was superseded)\n\n**Entities exposed** (per Sergio's 2026-06-30 email): customers, projects, users, userTasks, obligations, projectObligations.\n\n**Auth**: OAuth2 client credentials against Azure AD, configured at the collection level. Fill in `clientId` / `clientSecret` via a Postman *environment* (not committed here) — see the companion `Strategos-BC-Sandbox.postman_environment.json` file.\n\nSecurity note: this collection file itself carries no secrets and is safe to share/commit. The environment file with the real client_id/client_secret should NOT be committed to git or shared outside the team; rotate the secret if it ever leaks.\n\n**Write operations (Create/Update/Delete)**: only GET was confirmed by Sergio's emails and only GET is implemented on the Strategos side (`app/integrations/business_central/client.py` — by deliberate design, per `docs/backlog.md`, Business Central is the system of record and this platform is read-only for BC-owned entities in this round). Whether the underlying BC custom API pages also accept POST/PATCH/DELETE has **not** been confirmed with Becentis. Standard BC \"API page\" objects default to allowing insert/modify/delete unless the AL page explicitly disables them, so it is plausible but unverified. The Create/Update/Delete requests below exist so you can test that empirically against the RESTSTR sandbox — before relying on them:\n1. Run `Metadata > Get $metadata` and check each EntityType's properties/annotations for `Capabilities.InsertRestrictions` / `UpdateRestrictions` / `DeleteRestrictions` or read-only markers.\n2. Field names in the request bodies below are **best-guess camelCase** derived from Strategos' internal DTOs (`app/integrations/business_central/models.py`) — they have not been confirmed against BC's actual OData field names. Adjust them to match `$metadata` before trusting a non-404/405 response.\n3. PATCH/DELETE send `If-Match: *` to skip optimistic-concurrency checks; swap in a real `@odata.etag` value if BC rejects the wildcard.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
